commitResults.messageBody:
The code base has become too long in Duke.java.

This makes it hard to read and add code into existing codebase.

Let's refactor and abstract out methods to improve readability.

Current naming conventions are not in imperative form.

Let's change them to imperative form.

The current Duke does not enable a saving feature.

This makes the chatbot lose all its data once the program ends.

Let's enable a saving feature through file reader and file writer.

The chatbot still recognises date and time as strings.

We can do better than that. We can make sure the date gets recognised as date objects.

Let's parse the string date into the date object to create the date.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-MoreOOP Refactor code to abstract out more classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Current state has everything contained within Duke class.

This is not ideal for scaling of code.

Let's refactor the code to include the Ui class, Storage class, Parser class and Tasklist class.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-Packages Organise classes into suitable java packages
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently there's no packaging for the classes.

This could lead to confusion as more classes are created.

Let's package the classes into various packages to organise them.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-JUnit Add several JUnit tests to ensure methods used are working well
commitResults.messageBody:
Codebase does not have unit testing right now.

Unit Testing can be helpful in identifying bugs early.

Let's include JUnit tests to make sure code is tested regularly.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-JavaDoc Include JavaDocs for the codebase.
commitResults.messageBody:
Current codebase does not have JavaDocs for documentation.

This makes it hard to understand code and debugging.

Let's include JavaDocs for all public methods and classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-CodingStandard Fix Code styling via coding standards.
commitResults.messageBody:
Current code base has some issues regarding styling that violate coding standards.

Implementing the same coding standard will help increase readability of code.

Let's adjust the styling mistakes and rectify them according to coding standards.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-9 Find tasks based on description
commitResults.messageBody:
Current implementation does not allow users to search for a task.

Not being able to search in a long list might be problematic.

Let's create a search function.

Current implementation has no way to check if style is consistent.

This leads to inconsistency.

Let's include a way to check for styling.

Current state still uses a text based UI.

This is not user friendly.

Let's include a GUI into the chatbot to improve the user experience.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change Font Family For Send Button
Fix Bugs Regarding Date Format When Parsing Date
Add Changes Based On Reviews On Pull Requests.
Update Storage and TaskList to include Assertions
commitResults.messageBody:
Assertions are not used to check if tasks has indeed been added or deleted. Assertions are also not used to check if the directories has been created for the text file.

Using assertions asserts that tasks has been added for the various methods that add tasks to the tasklist. Also, it ensures that a new directory has indeed been created if the text file for storage does not exist.

Let's
Use Assertion to ensure that tasks have been added and deleted accordingly.
Use Assertions to ensure that the file directory has indeed been created.

Code Quality was not adhered to for Parser. Magic Numbers were being used for the indexing of substrings.

This makes code written hard to understand for readers of code base.

Let's,
Include constants for the different magic numbers so that the code is easier to understand.

Current codebase still contains redundant code.

This overcomplicates the code base for future development.

Let's
Remove the redundant code and clean up the code base.

commitResults.messageTitle: Create extension of add tasks feature to include detecting duplicates.
commitResults.messageBody:
Current implementation allows duplicate tasks to be added.

This causes unnecessary trouble for the user, as adding duplicates does not add value.

Let's
Include a mechanism to check for duplicates based on description and dates and alert user if duplicates are added.

commitResults.messageTitle: Changed background image and edited fonts

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently there's not user guide available.

This makes it hard for beginner users to use the chatbot.

Let's
Include the necessary features and examples on how to use them in the user guide.
